            <div type="translation">
            <p>For the beloved. For freedmen and -women and their descendants.</p></div>

            <div type="commentary">
            <p>Line 2 is restored as carrissimo (dat. sing.) assuming it would modify an
                    individualâ€™s name that came after and before libertis. Based on the established formula, it is likely that there
                    would have been an individual(s) named at the start of the epitaph. (c.f. CIL
                    6.39654). Similar formulae also help to date this inscription to the 1st century
                    CE (e.g., CIL 6. 19237). </p></div>
            

